		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30716045">Well, it's the same with the film and video game industries: visual media is expensive and a single financial bomb can result in the studio being closed and people out of work. <br />
<br />
I'd say the bigger problem is the anime industry's reliance on adaptations. I don't know the exact ratio, but I'd imagine the amount of adaptations versus anime-original series is a pretty huge difference. 10:1, maybe? It makes me not care about anime very much when I can simply consume these works in their original form. Adaptations are almost always worse than the source material, anyway. </div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://img541.imageshack.us/img541/6581/v46o.png" /><!--center--></div></div></td>
