		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30716143">It seems that much of what I was planning to say has already been said, which I'm a little sad about because this topic was my idea and I wanted to ramble about it.<br />
<br />
That said, here's some interesting raw data for you guys on the subject that I gathered in advance.<br />
<br />
I counted every single TV anime made in the last 5 years, and seperated them into Original (non-sequel/remake/etc, in other words), and sequels. I then calculated what percentage of anime that year was made up of sequels.<br />
<br />
<div class="spoiler"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.nextSibling.nextSibling.style.display='block';this.style.display='none';" value="Show spoiler"> <span class="spoiler_content" style="display:none"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.parentNode.style.display='none';this.parentNode.parentNode.childNodes[0].style.display='block';" value="Hide spoiler"><br>2009: 26%<br />
<br />
O - 86<br />
S - 31<br />
<br />
<br />
2010: 25%<br />
<br />
O - 79<br />
S - 27<br />
<br />
<br />
2011: 20%<br />
<br />
O - 104<br />
S - 26<br />
<br />
<br />
2012: 27%<br />
<br />
O - 107<br />
S - 40<br />
<br />
<br />
2013: 35%<br />
<br />
O - 116<br />
S - 65<!--spoiler--></span></div><br />
<br />
In other words, last year featured a whopping 25 more sequels than any other year of the past half-decade.<br />
<br />
This is a big part of why, for several months not too long ago, I completely lost interest in anime. Take note of which anime were heavily talked-about last year. There were a couple of underground hits - Uchouten Kazoku and Kyousogiga - pluss the big popular ones, Kill la Kill and of course Shingeki no Kyojin.<br />
<br />
That was pretty much it for the whole fucking year. Other than that, it was all about the sequels!<br />
<br />
However, though many of these sequels were superlative - in fact, Monogatari Second Season is firmly my anime of the year for 2013 - it becomes so hard to put up with all the bullshit that the anime industry throws at us when there is such an utter death of creative new ideas coming out of the woodwork. Though 2014 has already been quite sequel-heavy, we've already had Ping Pong and Knights of Sidonia, so I'm set for good new ideas, personally.<br />
<br />
In other words, I'm not necessarily against the concept of more sequels being made - just that they seem to be filler for the absence of original concepts.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://i.imgur.com/Y1FB912.png" /><br />
<span style="font-size: 150%;"><!--link--><a href="http://theotaku2anime.wordpress.com/2014/04/28/joe-the-lion-crackpot-jojolion-theory-time/#more-1192" rel="nofollow">Latest Blog: Joe The Lion - Crackpot JoJolion Theory Time!</a></div></td>
